This recipe features @koiosbeveragecorp drinks which enhance ketone production for better brain production in order to stay sharp throughout the day! #KOIOS is an all natural, organic drink that’s wonderfully flavored and easy drinking.

TAG A FRIEND TO SHARE THIS RECIPE! Your taste buds and belly will thank me!

What you need
1️⃣ 1–2 cup deseeded watermelon

Get #koios for yourself or your friends/family directly by ordering at koiosbeveragecorp.com or clicking the link in their bio!

The brand new Rossa violet is BACK in stock (they sold out when they launched last week in 13 hours) 😳 This is my first time using it.. as you can see its a GORGEOUS PURPLE UNDERTONE and it’s great for ALL skin tones! Its very easy to apply, goes on smooth, doesn’t streak, you can make it as dark as you want AND it doesn’t stain your clothes... 💜 Definitely a MUST TRY!

Last week was the owner of @rossaselftanning ‘s birthday and for that he is giving YOU a gift! In honor of his 34th birthday my code is 34% off for one day only!!! Then goes back to 15% - All products including apparel just use code: PHFIT! 😘

Happy 4th of July babes! ❤️Hope you all enjoy this DELICIOUS SMOOTHIE recipe! And for all my pregnant mommy’s out there.. I explain the benefits 📝 of each ingredient and how it can help while creating your little nugget! 👶🏼 I’ve listed the shake below.. THIS IS FOR ALL MY CHOCOLATE LOVERS OUT THERE:

1 large banana frozen 
2 tablespoons of natural peanut butter 
2 dates pited 
1 table unsweetened cocoa powder 
1 cup of almond milk 
1 tablespoon of cacao nibs (for the chocolate effect) 
1 tablespoon hemps seeds 
1 scoop #Livbody chocolate mocha protein

Use code Paige20 for 20% off @livbody 🤤

Win Rossa’s best selling products. See below to enter.

1. LIKE this post 👍⁠
2. FOLLOW @Rossaselftanning AND @Paigehathaway
3. TAG A FRIEND who would love @rossaselftanning, ⁠the more people you tag the higher your chances of winning!

Contest end on Tuesday 7/19 at 11:59pm PST. Winners will be contacted via private DM and announced on my Instagram only. We would never ask you for your personal banking information. I’ll choose winners Wednesday. Contest is not affiliated with Instagram! Let’s beat skin cancer together and Good luck!✨⁠

node.text:
What an incredible achievement by Ashley Flannery who says “After having 2 children and multiple cesarean sections, working out was not the easiest to maintain and achieve. This challenge was able to give me the confidence and my body back the way that I wished for.” - @aflannery26

Ashley… What an inspiration you are to me and so many other woman! I am so happy you trusted in the @Fitin5challenge and myself! I am also glad you trusted in yourself and in the process. You are living proof that hard work, consistency and dedication always wins!!

Next challenge starts August 1st and is already half way full — HURRY, TAP IN BIO AND EMAIL ME TODAY!

node.text:
IT HAS BEEN A JOURNEY…. 
All my life I was in seemly good shape. I was always the “skinny girl” but after I grew up I just didn’t want to be the thin girl anymore because I didn’t feel womanly. When I was introduced to weight lifting I fell in love with how it transformed me from the inside out. I became a stronger more confident person. 

Once I got pregnant my body image issues tanked. This isn’t something a lot of women will openly admit but I didn’t particularly enjoy being pregnant. Maybe it’s because I felt like I had no control over my own body. Maybe it was the pressure of looking like girls on social media who seemed “super fit” 7-8 months pregnant. I mean I did gain over 40+ lbs during my pregnancy and my belly had its own zip code.

I’ll be honest, my postpartum journey wasn’t what I thought, I always heard because I was active before baby… that my pre-baby body would come back quick, which wasn’t the case for me. I remember one time sitting on the couch a couple of months after giving birth and crying. This wasn’t about societal pressure to “bounce back”, or that I hated when someone touched my stomach… It was about me and how I felt inside.

I am telling you all this for those who feel defeated or long to get their “old selves” back — physically and mentally! I’m saying this for all the people who think that they can’t do it. I understand. I was there and for most of us… IT TAKES TIME! It’s takes the daily grind and dedication that you don’t see online. It takes a lot of courage to push through the hard times. 

It’s crazy and amazing what WE ALL ARE capable of.
LIFE IS A JOURNEY… it’s a evolving beautiful journey!
